<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="32" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="17" pageNumber="32">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="17" pageNumber="32">
This species has been recorded in Egypt (the Sinai Peninsula) and Israel. Notwithstanding, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kovarik, F" journalOrPublisher="Euscorpius" pageId="29" pageNumber="44" pagination="1 - 16" title="Review of Tunisian Species of the Genus Buthus with Descriptions of Two New Species and a Discussion of Ehrenberg's Types (Scorpiones: Buthidae)." url="http://www.science.marshall.edu/fet/euscorpius/p2006_34.pdf" volume="34" year="2006">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Kovařík">Kovarik</normalizedToken>
(2006)
</bibRefCitation>
considered this species to be a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. intumescens" pageId="17" pageNumber="32" rank="species" species="intumescens">B. intumescens</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
